Source: Gooch, Brad. City Poet: The Life and Times of Frank O’Hara. (1993)
Quote:
He said, “There’s a special train. After you’ve done the Third Avenue bars, you take it at Fifty-third and Third and it goes right to West Eighth Street. And then you have all of Eighth Street.” 
- O’Hara, new to Manhattan, recalls cruising advice from his old roommate, Eliot House
